I walked past this place a few times over the last few weeks and told myself I’d try it asap. There’s something about spots like this that scream “try me bc I’m def better than most of the other restaurants around me”. I’m glad I tried it because the food was very rich in flavor, and price was amazing for what you get. Meat was tender and lots of great options to choose from on the menu.  Read the following part with a grain of sand : I gave this restaurant 5 stars. I believe it’s a 5 star restaurant based on the merit given above. However, I feel it’s necessary to add that I got very sick almost immediately after finishing my steak California style burrito. Now the reason I didn’t start the review with this is because me getting sick could be due to numerous factors, such as what I ate for lunch earlier in the day that may not have sat well with the contents in the burrito. I’m not sure if it’s the meat that made me sick, or the fries inside the burrito. Lots of external factors to consider - so I’m not blaming this restaurant for getting me sick because I don’t know if that’s fair. But I did get sick and throw up all the food. This is the first time in my life that’s ever happened to me and I don’t deal with any allergies either. My friend had a few steak tacos and he did not get sick.

You know that restaurant that you compare everything else to, that’s Angela’s for me. I haven’t eaten there since 2002, due to numerous relocations for work, but whether it was San Antonio, SoCal, or Southeast Michigan,I have yet since had such a great burrito. It pains me so not have a great Mexican style restaurant that I had to write this 18 year old review. Especially seeing how Google Maps and the reviews weren’t even created yet in 2002.
